column5: i love lime crime, you look great!!! 💚

i was one of the few unlucky people who had the skin reaction to Lamictal (the upper body rash that can turn into Stevens-Johnson syndrome if left untreated), which really really sucked for me because it was actually working well for me. i would generally recommend Lamictal though because the chances of getting the skin reaction are relatively low.
the sleepiness on seroquel was too much for me (i was a fucking zombie), but i hope you have minimal side effects with it! i’m on 30mg of abilify now and am having much better luck with it 💖
